link:reference.tin-part:Note: Value reported using this element must be element available in taxonomies used in filing, including extension taxonomy. Example of how pattern for reported value would appear, but may not necessarily be reported for this element, is: "http://fasb.org/us-gaap-ebp/2025#EmployeeBenefitPlanAsset". There is no limit to number of values that could be reported. Additional values are required to be space-separated and alphabetically ordered.

link:reference.tin-part:Note: Element is intended to convey location within statement of change in net asset available for benefit of element identified in tin-part:AlternateElement, when element identified in tin-part:AlternateElement is not presented separately.
If element is not presented separately in statement of change in net asset, element identified in tin-part:AlternateElement is used to convey location within statement of change in net asset.

Element is intended to be used for investment amount, measured at contract value, when there is no plan interest in master trust. Element intended to be used for amount of plan interest in master trust, measured at contract value, is identified first in tin-part:AlternateElement. Element intended to be used for total investment amount, measured at contract value, when plan has interest in master trust is identified second in tin-part:AlternateElement.

Element is intended to be used for investment amount, measured at fair and contract value, when there is no plan interest in master trust. Element intended to be used for amount of plan interest in master trust, measured at fair and contract value, is identified first in tin-part:AlternateElement. Element intended to be used for total investment amount, measured at fair and contract value, when plan has interest in master trust is identified second in tin-part:AlternateElement.

Element is intended to be used for investment amount, measured at fair value, when there is no plan interest in master trust. Element intended to be used for amount of plan interest in master trust, measured at fair value, is identified first in tin-part:AlternateElement. Element intended to be used for total investment amount, measured at fair value, when plan has interest in master trust is identified second in tin-part:AlternateElement.

Plan-specific member within domain identified in tin-part:AlternateElement is intended to be in following format, [EBP] Employer Identification Number [0-9]{2}-[0-9]{7}-Plan Number [0-9]{3} (for example, standard label, EBP 12-3456789-001 [Member] with element name, EBP12-3456789-001Member).
Element is to be used on every XBRL fact tagged in each Employee Benefit Plan filing.

Element is intended to convey location within statement of change in net asset available for benefit of element identified in tin-part:AlternateElement, when element identified in tin-part:AlternateElement is not presented separately.
Element is modeled from perspective of statement of net asset available for benefit.
Element is intended to be used for any employee stock purchase, savings, or similar plan reporting plan equity.
